{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":838,"text":"Cancer affects all of us --"},{"time":3045,"text":"especially the ones that come\nback over and over again,"},{"time":6436,"text":"the highly invasive\nand drug-resistant ones,"},{"time":9456,"text":"the ones that defy medical treatment,"},{"time":11859,"text":"even when we throw our best drugs at them."},{"time":15247,"text":"Engineering at the molecular level,"},{"time":18191,"text":"working at the smallest of scales,"},{"time":20863,"text":"can provide exciting new ways"},{"time":23410,"text":"to fight the most aggressive\nforms of cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27260,"text":"Cancer is a very clever disease."},{"time":30346,"text":"There are some forms of cancer,"},{"time":31947,"text":"which, fortunately, we've learned\nhow to address relatively well"},{"time":36706,"text":"with known and established\ndrugs and surgery."},{"time":40627,"text":"But there are some forms of cancer"},{"time":42628,"text":"that don't respond to these approaches,"},{"time":44884,"text":"and the tumor survives or comes back,"},{"time":47536,"text":"even after an onslaught of drugs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50053,"text":"We can think of these\nvery aggressive forms of cancer"},{"time":54071,"text":"as kind of supervillains in a comic book."},{"time":57455,"text":"They're clever, they're adaptable,"},{"time":60184,"text":"and they're very good at staying alive."},{"time":63744,"text":"And, like most supervillains these days,"},{"time":66996,"text":"their superpowers come\nfrom a genetic mutation."},{"time":72740,"text":"The genes that are modified\ninside these tumor cells"},{"time":75706,"text":"can enable and encode for new\nand unimagined modes of survival,"},{"time":80997,"text":"allowing the cancer cell to live through"},{"time":83496,"text":"even our best chemotherapy treatments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86789,"text":"One example is a trick\nin which a gene allows a cell,"},{"time":91320,"text":"even as the drug approaches the cell,"},{"time":94390,"text":"to push the drug out,"},{"time":97850,"text":"before the drug can have any effect."},{"time":100047,"text":"Imagine -- the cell effectively\nspits out the drug."},{"time":104393,"text":"This is just one example\nof the many genetic tricks"},{"time":107347,"text":"in the bag of our supervillain, cancer."},{"time":109971,"text":"All due to mutant genes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112717,"text":"So, we have a supervillain\nwith incredible superpowers."},{"time":117462,"text":"And we need a new and powerful\nmode of attack."},{"time":121704,"text":"Actually, we can turn off a gene."},{"time":125328,"text":"The key is a set of molecules\nknown as siRNA."},{"time":129143,"text":"siRNA are short sequences of genetic code"},{"time":133253,"text":"that guide a cell to block a certain gene."},{"time":136982,"text":"Each siRNA molecule\ncan turn off a specific gene"},{"time":140581,"text":"inside the cell."},{"time":143292,"text":"For many years since its discovery,"},{"time":145337,"text":"scientists have been very excited"},{"time":147311,"text":"about how we can apply\nthese gene blockers in medicine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151216,"text":"But, there is a problem."},{"time":152958,"text":"siRNA works well inside the cell."},{"time":155854,"text":"But if it gets exposed to the enzymes"},{"time":158872,"text":"that reside in our bloodstream\nor our tissues,"},{"time":161396,"text":"it degrades within seconds."},{"time":163769,"text":"It has to be packaged, protected\nthrough its journey through the body"},{"time":168109,"text":"on its way to the final target\ninside the cancer cell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171740,"text":"So, here's our strategy."},{"time":174468,"text":"First, we'll dose the cancer cell\nwith siRNA, the gene blocker,"},{"time":178295,"text":"and silence those survival genes,"},{"time":179915,"text":"and then we'll whop it with a chemo drug."},{"time":182501,"text":"But how do we carry that out?"},{"time":184764,"text":"Using molecular engineering,"},{"time":187705,"text":"we can actually design a superweapon"},{"time":191648,"text":"that can travel through the bloodstream."},{"time":193923,"text":"It has to be tiny enough\nto get through the bloodstream,"},{"time":196943,"text":"it's got to be small enough\nto penetrate the tumor tissue,"},{"time":200368,"text":"and it's got to be tiny enough\nto be taken up inside the cancer cell."},{"time":205049,"text":"To do this job well,"},{"time":206675,"text":"it has to be about one one-hundredth\nthe size of a human hair."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212224,"text":"Let's take a closer look\nat how we can build this nanoparticle."},{"time":217146,"text":"First, let's start\nwith the nanoparticle core."},{"time":219567,"text":"It's a tiny capsule that contains\nthe chemotherapy drug."},{"time":224089,"text":"This is the poison that will\nactually end the tumor cell's life."},{"time":228152,"text":"Around this core, we'll wrap a very thin,"},{"time":231961,"text":"nanometers-thin blanket of siRNA."},{"time":234818,"text":"This is our gene blocker."},{"time":237093,"text":"Because siRNA is strongly\nnegatively charged,"},{"time":240706,"text":"we can protect it"},{"time":242287,"text":"with a nice, protective layer\nof positively charged polymer."},{"time":247503,"text":"The two oppositely charged\nmolecules stick together"},{"time":250784,"text":"through charge attraction,"},{"time":252244,"text":"and that provides us\nwith a protective layer"},{"time":254402,"text":"that prevents the siRNA\nfrom degrading in the bloodstream."},{"time":258106,"text":"We're almost done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259430,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":260914,"text":"But there is one more big obstacle\nwe have to think about."},{"time":265016,"text":"In fact, it may be the biggest\nobstacle of all."},{"time":267432,"text":"How do we deploy this superweapon?"},{"time":269430,"text":"I mean, every good weapon\nneeds to be targeted,"},{"time":272008,"text":"we have to target this superweapon\nto the supervillain cells"},{"time":276097,"text":"that reside in the tumor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278071,"text":"But our bodies have a natural\nimmune-defense system:"},{"time":281916,"text":"cells that reside in the bloodstream"},{"time":283891,"text":"and pick out things that don't belong,"},{"time":286260,"text":"so that it can destroy or eliminate them."},{"time":288583,"text":"And guess what? Our nanoparticle\nis considered a foreign object."},{"time":293718,"text":"We have to sneak our nanoparticle\npast the tumor defense system."},{"time":297841,"text":"We have to get it past this mechanism\nof getting rid of the foreign object"},{"time":304119,"text":"by disguising it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305563,"text":"So we add one more\nnegatively charged layer"},{"time":309932,"text":"around this nanoparticle,"},{"time":311280,"text":"which serves two purposes."},{"time":313140,"text":"First, this outer layer is one\nof the naturally charged,"},{"time":317132,"text":"highly hydrated polysaccharides\nthat resides in our body."},{"time":321456,"text":"It creates a cloud of water molecules\naround the nanoparticle"},{"time":326313,"text":"that gives us an invisibility\ncloaking effect."},{"time":330257,"text":"This invisibility cloak allows\nthe nanoparticle"},{"time":332998,"text":"to travel through the bloodstream"},{"time":334628,"text":"long and far enough to reach the tumor,"},{"time":337417,"text":"without getting eliminated by the body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340121,"text":"Second, this layer contains molecules"},{"time":344537,"text":"which bind specifically to our tumor cell."},{"time":348190,"text":"Once bound, the cancer cell\ntakes up the nanoparticle,"},{"time":352734,"text":"and now we have our nanoparticle\ninside the cancer cell"},{"time":357132,"text":"and ready to deploy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359304,"text":"Alright! I feel the same way. Let's go!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":361565,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":368057,"text":"The siRNA is deployed first."},{"time":372287,"text":"It acts for hours,"},{"time":373937,"text":"giving enough time to silence\nand block those survival genes."},{"time":379398,"text":"We have now disabled\nthose genetic superpowers."},{"time":383725,"text":"What remains is a cancer cell\nwith no special defenses."},{"time":386978,"text":"Then, the chemotherapy drug\ncomes out of the core"},{"time":389904,"text":"and destroys the tumor cell\ncleanly and efficiently."},{"time":394228,"text":"With sufficient gene blockers,"},{"time":396589,"text":"we can address many\ndifferent kinds of mutations,"},{"time":399823,"text":"allowing the chance to sweep out tumors,"},{"time":402208,"text":"without leaving behind any bad guys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404811,"text":"So, how does our strategy work?"},{"time":409543,"text":"We've tested these nanostructure\nparticles in animals"},{"time":413528,"text":"using a highly aggressive form\nof triple-negative breast cancer."},{"time":417135,"text":"This triple-negative breast cancer\nexhibits the gene"},{"time":419714,"text":"that spits out cancer drug\nas soon as it is delivered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423742,"text":"Usually, doxorubicin -- let's call\nit \"dox\" -- is the cancer drug"},{"time":428937,"text":"that is the first line of treatment\nfor breast cancer."},{"time":432178,"text":"So, we first treated our animals\nwith a dox core, dox only."},{"time":438661,"text":"The tumor slowed their rate of growth,"},{"time":440892,"text":"but they still grew rapidly,"},{"time":442356,"text":"doubling in size\nover a period of two weeks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445297,"text":"Then, we tried\nour combination superweapon."},{"time":449415,"text":"A nanolayer particle with siRNA\nagainst the chemo pump,"},{"time":453851,"text":"plus, we have the dox in the core."},{"time":456870,"text":"And look -- we found that not only\ndid the tumors stop growing,"},{"time":461209,"text":"they actually decreased in size"},{"time":463749,"text":"and were eliminated in some cases."},{"time":466188,"text":"The tumors were actually regressing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469859,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":477820,"text":"What's great about this approach\nis that it can be personalized."},{"time":481652,"text":"We can add many different layers of siRNA"},{"time":484512,"text":"to address different mutations\nand tumor defense mechanisms."},{"time":488094,"text":"And we can put different drugs\ninto the nanoparticle core."},{"time":491946,"text":"As doctors learn how to test patients"},{"time":495177,"text":"and understand certain\ntumor genetic types,"},{"time":498975,"text":"they can help us determine which patients\ncan benefit from this strategy"},{"time":502741,"text":"and which gene blockers we can use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506410,"text":"Ovarian cancer strikes\na special chord with me."},{"time":509337,"text":"It is a very aggressive cancer,"},{"time":511334,"text":"in part because it's discovered\nat very late stages,"},{"time":514243,"text":"when it's highly advanced"},{"time":515714,"text":"and there are a number\nof genetic mutations."},{"time":518566,"text":"After the first round of chemotherapy,"},{"time":521579,"text":"this cancer comes back\nfor 75 percent of patients."},{"time":526333,"text":"And it usually comes back\nin a drug-resistant form."},{"time":530215,"text":"High-grade ovarian cancer"},{"time":531933,"text":"is one of the biggest\nsupervillains out there."},{"time":534124,"text":"And we're now directing our superweapon"},{"time":536060,"text":"toward its defeat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539375,"text":"As a researcher,"},{"time":540661,"text":"I usually don't get to work with patients."},{"time":544164,"text":"But I recently met a mother"},{"time":546605,"text":"who is an ovarian cancer survivor,\nMimi, and her daughter, Paige."},{"time":552257,"text":"I was deeply inspired\nby the optimism and strength"},{"time":556385,"text":"that both mother and daughter displayed"},{"time":559495,"text":"and by their story of courage and support."},{"time":563119,"text":"At this event, we spoke\nabout the different technologies"},{"time":566546,"text":"directed at cancer."},{"time":568355,"text":"And Mimi was in tears"},{"time":569688,"text":"as she explained how learning\nabout these efforts"},{"time":572539,"text":"gives her hope for future generations,"},{"time":574773,"text":"including her own daughter."},{"time":577449,"text":"This really touched me."},{"time":579524,"text":"It's not just about building\nreally elegant science."},{"time":583140,"text":"It's about changing people's lives."},{"time":586330,"text":"It's about understanding\nthe power of engineering"},{"time":589565,"text":"on the scale of molecules."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591470,"text":"I know that as students like Paige\nmove forward in their careers,"},{"time":595577,"text":"they'll open new possibilities"},{"time":597041,"text":"in addressing some of the big\nhealth problems in the world --"},{"time":600455,"text":"including ovarian cancer, neurological\ndisorders, infectious disease --"},{"time":606104,"text":"just as chemical engineering has\nfound a way to open doors for me,"},{"time":610437,"text":"and has provided a way of engineering"},{"time":613095,"text":"on the tiniest scale,\nthat of molecules,"},{"time":616651,"text":"to heal on the human scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619797,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620979,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}